<div id="main_content">
	<h2>UCF Science Camps Focus on Roller Coasters, Forensics, Hurricanes and More </h2>
	
	<p class="article_info">
		
			By Courtney Gilmartin
		
		<span class="date">May 29, 2008</span></p>
	
	
	
		<div class="article_img" style="width: 261px;">

			<img alt="Article Main Picture" src="../resources/sites/UCF/content/live/NEWS/1000/NE1460/en_US/laserscrop.jpg" height="196" width="261"  /> 
			
				<p class="photo_credit">Photo: UCF News file</p>
			
			<p>At the first summer science camp, students will learn about mirrors, lenses, the primary colors of light and more.</p>
			
				<p class="note"><a class="full_photo" id="popup.jsp?article_id=002400414973f6b011a35d0fdff0013c">Full Photo</a></p>
			
			
			
			
					
						
						
						
					
			
			
			
					
						
						
						
					
			
			
			
		</div>
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
		
			<div id="related">
				<h3>Related Contacts and Links:</h3>
				<ul>
		
		<li>
		
			
				<h4><a href="mailto:mmckee@creol.ucf.edu">Mike McKee</a></h4>
			
			
			
			
		
		</li>
	
		
		<li>
		
			
				<h4><a href="mailto:cbinette@mail.ucf.edu">Chad Binette, News and Information</a></h4>
			
			
			
				<ul>
				<li>407-823-6312</li>
			
			</ul>
		
		</li>
	
	
	
		
		<li>
		
			<h4><a href="http://gogk12.optics.ucf.edu/camp/">CREOL Summer Science Camps</a></h4>
		
		</li>
	
	
	 </ul></div> 
	
	
			
	
	
	
	
		
	
	
		
	
	
		
	
	
		
	
	
		
	
	
		
	
	<div id="share">
		<ul><li><p id="print"><a href="javascript:window.print();">Print this Page</a></li></ul>
	
	</div>
	
	
	
	
		
			<p>Youths will learn what causes the feeling of weightlessness during long drops on roller coasters and solve crimes using hair and fingerprint analyses during summer science camps at the University of Central Florida.</p>
<p>The camps are geared towards highly motivated students in grades 3 through 12 who have an interest in science, mathematics and technology. Camps will focus on topics such as Amusement Park Physics, Forensics and Severe Storm Science.</p>
<p>UCF&rsquo;s Center for Research and Education in Optics and Lasers (CREOL) within the College of Optics and Photonics will host nine weekly camps, which begin June 9 and conclude the week of July 21. Each session is open to a maximum of 15 students from a particular grade range (grades 3-5, 6-8 or 9-12); some sessions already are full, while openings remain in others.</p>
<p>Students will participate in hands-on, team based activities developed by UCF scientists and educators and taught by UCF graduate students and local high school teachers. Organizers hope to inspire many of the campers to pursue careers in science, engineering and math.</p>
<p>&ldquo;There is such a need for homegrown scientists and engineers,&rdquo; says camp coordinator Mike McKee. &ldquo;These camps allow students to pursue a career in sciences in a fun way.&rdquo;</p>
<p>At the Kitchen Chemistry camp, students will learn what causes the fizz in soda. During the Severe Storm Science week, they will learn what makes wind blow so hard during hurricanes.</p>
<p>Stimulating students&rsquo; minds with educational material during school breaks is important, McKee said, because &ldquo;if students turn into couch potatoes over the summer, their retention of math and sciences decreases when they go back to school.&rdquo;</p>
<p>The first session, &ldquo;Optics and Photonics,&rdquo; will begin the week of June 9, and the last camp will be held the week of July 21. Each camp runs Monday through Friday and starts at 9 a.m. and ends at 4 p.m. daily. The cost is $450 per week, and UCF employees receive a 20 percent discount.&nbsp; Lunch, snacks and all materials are included.</p>
<p>For more information about the camps or to register, visit <a href="http://gogk12.optics.ucf.edu/camp/">http://gogk12.optics.ucf.edu/camp/</a>.</p>
<hr />
<p><strong>UCF Stands For Opportunity: </strong><span style="font-weight: normal">The University of Central Florida is a metropolitan research university that ranks as the 6th largest in the nation with more than 48,000 students. UCF's first classes were offered in 1968. The university offers impressive academic and research environments that power the region's economic development. UCF's culture of opportunity is driven by our diversity, Orlando environment, history of entrepreneurship and our youth, relevance and energy. For more information visit <a href="index.html">http://news.ucf.edu</a>.</span></p>
		
	
